1
00:00:01,602 --> 00:00:04,629
If you don't know how to use a
computer, we will teach you here.

2
00:00:04,738 --> 00:00:07,572
Most jobs require at least
basic word processing skills.

3
00:00:07,641 --> 00:00:10,304
We try to get you up
to 50 words per minute.

4
00:00:10,410 --> 00:00:14,245
We also have a course in how
to talk to someone in an interview.

5
00:00:14,314 --> 00:00:16,840
Stuff like what
employers are looking for,

6
00:00:16,917 --> 00:00:18,476
how to turn negatives
into positives.

7
00:00:18,585 --> 00:00:20,763
We can also provide clothes
for the interview if you need them.

8
00:00:20,787 --> 00:00:23,586
People donate shoes
and suits all the time.

9
00:00:24,191 --> 00:00:27,457
What if I had a
history with drugs?

10
00:00:28,161 --> 00:00:29,959
That is nothing
to be ashamed of.

11
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:31,908
Many of our clients have
struggled with addiction,

12
00:00:31,932 --> 00:00:35,130
and if you want to get
clean, we'll help you do that.

13
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:36,693
And what if I have a kid?

14
00:00:37,804 --> 00:00:38,931
No one to help you?

15
00:00:39,006 --> 00:00:43,501
If I need someone to watch her
while I'm in a class or on an interview,

16
00:00:44,177 --> 00:00:45,702
could you help with that?

17
00:00:45,812 --> 00:00:47,212
We do not provide child care.

18
00:00:47,281 --> 00:00:49,648
Actually, it's something
that comes up often.

19
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:51,808
I would love to
be able to do it.

20
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:53,854
I just don't have the resources.

21
00:00:53,954 --> 00:00:56,480
But it's definitely
on the wish list.

22
00:00:57,357 --> 00:01:02,125
Okay. Okay, uh,
thank you. I'll be back.

23
00:01:02,329 --> 00:01:03,640
I have to take this.

24
00:01:03,664 --> 00:01:05,895
Yes, please come back.
We'll get you started.

25
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:09,169
It was nice to meet
you, Benjamin.

26
00:01:09,236 --> 00:01:10,829
Hey, Oscar.

27
00:01:11,705 --> 00:01:14,231
Ugh! That is too bad.

28
00:01:14,341 --> 00:01:16,310
Did they tell you why?

29
00:01:23,617 --> 00:01:24,744
Yeah.

30
00:01:26,119 --> 00:01:27,143
Mmm-hmm.

31
00:01:27,220 --> 00:01:30,782
Well, look, you know what?
Sometimes you just don't get the job.

32
00:01:30,891 --> 00:01:33,417
Oscar, I've got
to call you back.

33
00:01:35,195 --> 00:01:36,288
Uh...

34
00:01:37,864 --> 00:01:39,093
Uh, uh...

35
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:46,035
Benjamin! Benjamin, wait.

36
00:01:51,311 --> 00:01:52,939
Oh, my God.

37
00:02:03,056 --> 00:02:05,423
Somebody call an ambulance!

38
00:03:07,988 --> 00:03:10,548
Why am I watching
you cut your hair?

39
00:03:10,657 --> 00:03:13,991
If I do it at home, I'm the
one who has to clean it up.

40
00:03:14,061 --> 00:03:18,192
I was referring less to where
it's happening and more to why.

41
00:03:18,298 --> 00:03:20,199
New life, new look.

42
00:03:21,902 --> 00:03:24,895
Does that mean you
like your new life?

43
00:03:25,005 --> 00:03:26,997
If you're asking
if your job is safe,

44
00:03:27,074 --> 00:03:30,067
that depends on what you have
to say about the file you're holding.

45
00:03:30,177 --> 00:03:32,544
It doesn't seem
like much of a case.

46
00:03:32,646 --> 00:03:34,512
Although, I'm sure I'm wrong.

47
00:03:34,581 --> 00:03:36,573
You are. Tell me why.

48
00:03:36,683 --> 00:03:39,152
Guy collapsed after
being on his feet for hours

49
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:42,712
on a hot day without
breakfast, so that's really weird.

50
00:03:42,823 --> 00:03:47,420
ER found nothing wrong, then I
decided I should test his wallet.

51
00:03:47,527 --> 00:03:49,553
He's rich? That's why
we're taking the case?

52
00:03:49,663 --> 00:03:50,961
No, we're taking
the case because

53
00:03:51,031 --> 00:03:53,057
no one knows
what's wrong with him.

54
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:54,725
And he's rich.

55
00:03:57,938 --> 00:03:59,406
Dr. Adams.

56
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:01,541
Give her the file.

57
00:04:01,608 --> 00:04:03,167
This is my only copy.

58
00:04:04,544 --> 00:04:07,241
My MO depends
upon the use of a team.

59
00:04:07,347 --> 00:04:10,545
Definitionally, that involves
more than one person,

60
00:04:10,617 --> 00:04:11,915
so I really have no choice.

61
00:04:12,018 --> 00:04:14,112
Give her the file. You
can't afford a team.

62
00:04:14,454 --> 00:04:16,013
Adams is free.

63
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:18,923
And I'm referring both to her
availability and her price tag.

64
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:23,555
New girl meet newer
girl, and vice versa.

65
00:04:24,698 --> 00:04:26,189
You said we were
meeting for coffee.

66
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,667
Well, when someone
asks if you want coffee,

67
00:04:28,735 --> 00:04:30,931
they obviously don't
just mean coffee.

68
00:04:31,371 --> 00:04:34,899
Wait. Did you think I
was referring to sex?

69
00:04:34,975 --> 00:04:36,705
Would you shut the
blinds on your way out?

70
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:38,803
I thought you were
referring to talking.

71
00:04:38,912 --> 00:04:40,744
Talking about medicine.

72
00:04:40,814 --> 00:04:43,579
Specifically, as it refers to the
guy whose name is on the file

73
00:04:43,650 --> 00:04:45,642
she still hasn't handed you.

74
00:04:45,752 --> 00:04:49,621
I'm not working, House. I'm in the
process of looking for a paying job.

75
00:04:49,723 --> 00:04:52,215
And in the meantime, there's
no way a do-gooder like you

76
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,056
isn't volunteering
all over town,

77
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:56,323
ladling kittens, spaying soup.

78
00:04:56,429 --> 00:04:58,660
There's a free
clinic in Trenton.

79
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:01,367
Well, think of this
as today's free clinic.

80
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:03,300
Only with fewer
bums with herpes.

81
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:05,838
I don't think we actually
have much of a case.

82
00:05:05,939 --> 00:05:08,272
I think it's just dehydration.

83
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:11,587
What happened the
last time another doctor

84
00:05:11,611 --> 00:05:13,102
told you I was
wrong about a case?

85
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,614
I lost my job.

86
00:05:15,348 --> 00:05:16,680
But you saved a life.

87
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:23,654
Is an ultrasound really necessary?
I'm feeling much better now.

88
00:05:23,723 --> 00:05:25,715
A sudden collapse at
your age can indicate

89
00:05:25,792 --> 00:05:27,454
a deterioration in
the heart muscle,

90
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:29,690
a pretty serious condition.

91
00:05:29,796 --> 00:05:32,322
It could also just
be dehydration.

92
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:34,664
Next time, you could probably
drop the undercover act.

93
00:05:36,102 --> 00:05:40,130
I walk in in a suit, and they're
gonna put their best foot forward.

94
00:05:40,207 --> 00:05:42,176
Also I don't own a suit.

95
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:45,535
You give away millions,
and you don't own a suit?

96
00:05:45,645 --> 00:05:47,136
I gave those away too.

97
00:05:47,881 --> 00:05:49,873
One day I was writing a
check to my landscaper,

98
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,509
and it suddenly hit me,

99
00:05:51,585 --> 00:05:55,750
$6,000 to take out plants
and put in different plants

100
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:57,984
so I can look at them.

101
00:05:58,058 --> 00:06:00,254
Shouldn't I use that money
to do something important?

102
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,660
And by money, you
mean all your money.

103
00:06:03,730 --> 00:06:05,028
I started with $10 million,

104
00:06:05,098 --> 00:06:09,593
and then I couldn't think of
a reason not to give 20 or 40.

105
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:13,674
I figure I can live
on $25,000 a year.

106
00:06:14,074 --> 00:06:18,705
One room apartment, bus pass,
thrift stores, bare necessities.

107
00:06:18,778 --> 00:06:21,270
I still have my
software company.

108
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:24,545
And when I make more,
I'll give that away too.

109
00:06:24,618 --> 00:06:26,450
He's nuts. He's generous.

110
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:29,446
There's a neurological issue.
He's getting rid of everything.

111
00:06:29,556 --> 00:06:32,185
His echocardiogram was
negative for cardiomyopathy.

112
00:06:32,259 --> 00:06:34,558
Head CT showed no signs
of stroke or hemorrhage.

113
00:06:34,628 --> 00:06:36,028
He has one pair of pants!

114
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:37,860
Most people with
his kind of money

115
00:06:37,931 --> 00:06:40,901
are commissioning oil
paintings of their Yorkshire terrier.

116
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:44,233
Benjamin is sacrificing his
own comfort to help others.

117
00:06:44,304 --> 00:06:47,536
That's 'cause helping others
is his Yorkie oil painting.

118
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:49,906
That's good, not sick.

119
00:06:49,976 --> 00:06:51,706
That's naive and sick.

120
00:06:51,778 --> 00:06:54,056
You really want to improve
things, you do it through policy.

121
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,743
This guy empties his
pockets, what really changes?

122
00:06:56,816 --> 00:06:59,877
That's right. All those babies
with AIDS, they're just using us.

123
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:02,815
My parents had $800 between
them when they got here.

124
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:05,620
They scraped and borrowed
so we could go to good schools.

125
00:07:05,725 --> 00:07:09,093
And I worked my ass off.
No one gave me a handout.

126
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:10,255
It makes me work harder.

127
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:13,089
Rebuttal.

128
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:15,294
What's your evil plan?

129
00:07:15,368 --> 00:07:16,927
I object to your cynicism.

130
00:07:17,003 --> 00:07:18,995
It's been earned.
That's what I object to.

131
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:21,540
New Dean of Medicine has
an ethical obligation to come in

132
00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:23,940
with a completely open
mind about all employees,

133
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:27,139
thus letting me blithely run
roughshod for at least four weeks.

134
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,711
My theory is that you're
running a battery of tests

135
00:07:29,816 --> 00:07:31,546
to convince him that
you've saved his life,

136
00:07:31,651 --> 00:07:33,696
and then con him into funding
you to hire back your team.

137
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:35,211
What? Your old team?

138
00:07:36,056 --> 00:07:38,025
What? This is your new reality.

139
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:40,320
You've got your office,
you've got neighbors,

140
00:07:40,393 --> 00:07:42,055
you've got one
employee, one volunteer

141
00:07:42,162 --> 00:07:45,030
until she finds actual paid
work or gets sick of you.

142
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:47,999
I talked to Chase and Taub.
They're willing to come back.

143
00:07:48,969 --> 00:07:50,403
What about Thirteen?

144
00:07:50,503 --> 00:07:55,032
Not a good choice. She's not a
long-term, because she has no long-term.

145
00:07:55,909 --> 00:07:57,036
Not taking your calls?

146
00:07:58,712 --> 00:07:59,839
She will.

147
00:07:59,913 --> 00:08:01,404
Discharge the patient.

148
00:08:01,514 --> 00:08:04,916
Unexplained loss of consciousness
could be cardiomyopathy,

149
00:08:05,018 --> 00:08:07,078
global anoxia,
subarachnoid hemorrhage...

150
00:08:07,187 --> 00:08:09,884
Dehydration. He was given
fluids, and he got better.

151
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:11,400
And I'm sure your tests
have come up negative,

152
00:08:11,424 --> 00:08:13,325
or you'd have
shut me up already.

153
00:08:13,393 --> 00:08:14,554
Which means he goes home.

154
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:19,222
There is a symptom.

155
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,358
Extreme altruism.

156
00:08:25,772 --> 00:08:27,604
You've got two choices, House.

157
00:08:27,707 --> 00:08:29,801
You can recognize
that your patient is just

158
00:08:29,876 --> 00:08:32,038
a very nice, healthy
guy and send him home.

159
00:08:32,112 --> 00:08:34,707
Or you can consider
altruism a symptom,

160
00:08:34,781 --> 00:08:37,341
in which case, you
cannot take his money.

161
00:08:42,355 --> 00:08:44,551
Send him home.

162
00:08:44,624 --> 00:08:47,594
And check with admitting for
the net worth of all new patients.

163
00:08:59,906 --> 00:09:02,068
I'm not coming back, House.

164
00:09:05,145 --> 00:09:07,410
Technically, you're
back right now.

165
00:09:09,315 --> 00:09:11,910
I need you to stop calling me.

166
00:09:11,985 --> 00:09:13,886
The first 17 messages
were cute, but...

167
00:09:13,953 --> 00:09:16,218
I'm putting the
band back together.

168
00:09:16,289 --> 00:09:18,417
Interesting that you've
never showed up at my place,

169
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:20,118
what with your
love of annoying me

170
00:09:20,193 --> 00:09:23,061
and your inability to
take no for an answer.

171
00:09:23,129 --> 00:09:24,529
I'm guessing ankle monitor.

172
00:09:28,802 --> 00:09:32,261
Guilty as charged. Literally.

173
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:35,466
I'm not a doctor
any more, House.

174
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:39,569
The job went away
but not the profession.

175
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,715
You look healthy,
so that's not it.

176
00:09:45,151 --> 00:09:47,382
You met a boy or a girl,

177
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:50,322
fallen in love, wanna be happy.

178
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:54,418
You've decided to enjoy
what time you have left.

179
00:09:56,463 --> 00:09:57,897
You're going to Thailand.

180
00:10:00,233 --> 00:10:03,260
Girl. And MÃ½konos.

181
00:10:05,338 --> 00:10:06,829
Turns out I like boring.

182
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:09,000
No, you want to like boring.

183
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:10,386
But if you actually
liked boring,

184
00:10:10,410 --> 00:10:12,988
you would have figured that out
in fifth grade when you were bored.

185
00:10:13,012 --> 00:10:15,243
Please, stop calling me.

186
00:10:18,751 --> 00:10:20,083
No.

187
00:10:21,688 --> 00:10:24,487
You showed up to tell me that
you don't want to hear from me.

188
00:10:24,591 --> 00:10:26,924
That's a mixed signal.

189
00:10:26,993 --> 00:10:30,259
And I'm gonna choose to listen to
your actions rather than your words,

190
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:31,628
'cause they're more honest.

191
00:10:38,671 --> 00:10:40,139
I'm a little confused.

192
00:10:40,206 --> 00:10:42,471
The test is designed to
determine if your nerves are...

193
00:10:42,542 --> 00:10:45,512
No, I meant you're running
a test and discharging me?

194
00:10:45,612 --> 00:10:47,979
Was I dehydrated or not?

195
00:10:48,047 --> 00:10:50,983
I think so. But out of an
abundance of caution,

196
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:53,645
my colleague has taken it
upon herself to do one more test.

197
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,313
All right.

198
00:10:58,224 --> 00:10:59,852
You scare me a little.

199
00:11:02,529 --> 00:11:04,361
Why?

200
00:11:04,464 --> 00:11:07,559
I've been considering applying
to Doctors Without Borders,

201
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:09,067
going overseas awhile,

202
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:12,799
and that seems like a
huge sacrifice, but you...

203
00:11:12,872 --> 00:11:15,307
You don't scare her.
You make her feel guilty.

204
00:11:17,477 --> 00:11:20,037
You like your
life the way it is.

205
00:11:20,146 --> 00:11:22,047
Most people give the
minimum they have to give,

206
00:11:22,148 --> 00:11:23,639
so they can enjoy
what they have left.

207
00:11:23,716 --> 00:11:27,653
I guess my minimum
is just higher than most.

208
00:11:27,754 --> 00:11:30,485
Complete recruitment
and interference pattern.

209
00:11:30,557 --> 00:11:32,253
His leg muscles are fine.

210
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:34,554
I feel, uh, funny.

211
00:11:34,661 --> 00:11:36,391
Where? My chest.

212
00:11:36,496 --> 00:11:39,364
You're tachycardic. Your
heart's beating too fast.

213
00:11:39,465 --> 00:11:41,058
Unbelievable.

214
00:11:49,642 --> 00:11:51,770
Patient got tachycardic to 185.

215
00:11:51,844 --> 00:11:54,575
We pushed 18
milligrams adenosine.

216
00:11:54,681 --> 00:11:56,809
There's definitely
something wrong with him.

217
00:11:56,883 --> 00:12:00,012
Which is awesome. Now,
there's something to cure,

218
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:01,452
which means there's
something to be

219
00:12:01,521 --> 00:12:04,389
disproportionately
financially grateful for.

220
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:06,755
Morning. Got you coffee.

221
00:12:06,826 --> 00:12:08,021
Thanks.

222
00:12:08,094 --> 00:12:10,188
Arrhythmia could easily
have caused the collapse

223
00:12:10,263 --> 00:12:14,394
that landed Father Teresa
here in the first place.

224
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,662
Oh, it's fine. Keep it.

225
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:18,261
We looked at his
heart yesterday.

226
00:12:18,338 --> 00:12:20,068
Didn't see any
structural abnormalities.

227
00:12:20,173 --> 00:12:21,869
I'm thinking occult
long QT syndrome?

228
00:12:21,941 --> 00:12:22,941
What about Whipple's?

229
00:12:23,042 --> 00:12:25,588
If it was Whipple's, there'd be some
kind of neurological involvement.

230
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:28,047
You don't think defying
human nature is neurological?

231
00:12:28,114 --> 00:12:30,015
Racing heart, medical condition.

232
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:31,915
Bleeding heart,
stupid condition.

233
00:12:32,018 --> 00:12:33,662
Are you saying that
because you believe it,

234
00:12:33,686 --> 00:12:36,281
or because it's in your
financial best interests

235
00:12:36,389 --> 00:12:38,984
to think his generosity
isn't just temporary?

236
00:12:39,058 --> 00:12:42,586
I'm told that some
people are just nice.

237
00:12:42,662 --> 00:12:44,187
I'm trying to
embrace that wisdom.

238
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:47,257
Benjamin's been taking allergy
medication the last few weeks.

239
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:49,700
Long QT syndrome can
be medication-induced.

240
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:52,265
Flush him with saline. Get
rid of the antihistamines.

241
00:12:52,372 --> 00:12:54,273
Then do an EKG.

242
00:12:54,374 --> 00:12:56,366
No, wait. I'll do the flushing.

243
00:12:57,677 --> 00:12:59,407
And take the damn two dollars.

244
00:12:59,479 --> 00:13:00,913
She hasn't even
sipped the coffee.

245
00:13:04,717 --> 00:13:08,051
I just got so angry, you know?

246
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:10,681
So I made a terrible mistake,

247
00:13:10,757 --> 00:13:13,591
and now, I'm trying
to start my life over.

248
00:13:13,693 --> 00:13:15,753
To help people the
way I always wanted.

249
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:21,600
But my department got
defunded, and it's my fault.

